Memoize toggleGroup with useCallback:

```ts
const toggleGroup = useCallback((key: string) => {
  setExpandedGroups((prev) => {
    const next = new Set(prev);
    if (next.has(key)) next.delete(key);
    else next.add(key);
    return next;
  });
}, []); // no deps — uses functional updater form
```

Note that the inline lambdas passed to onToggle (e.g. `() => toggleGroup('food')`) will still create new references per render. If group rows are ever memoised, those lambdas should also be pre-bound or the onToggle signature should accept the key as a separate prop.

